original: Luxemburg, Tyskl. 37, Norge 38. Anst. v. ol. arkit :kont. i Gbg 33-35, v. stads-planekont. i Gbg 35-43. Sekr. i 40 års bost:komm. i Gbg. Stadsplanearkit. i Eskilstuna 43-46. Chef f. general-planekont. i Gbg fr. 47. Hobbies: s’egl:, fotogr.
translated: Luxemburg, born in Tyskl. in 1937, moved to Norway in 1938. Employed as an architectural assistant: worked at a planning office in Gothenburg from 1933 to 1935, and at a city planning office in Gothenburg from 1935 to 1943. Secretary in a 40-year housing committee in Gothenburg. City planning architect in Eskilstuna from 1943 to 1946. Head of the general planning office in Gothenburg starting from 1947. Hobbies include sailing and photography.
